            <section class="what-is-formatting" id="what-is-formatting">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 order-1 order-lg-2">
                            <img srcset="https://d1fd687oe6a92y.cloudfront.net/img/bookprep/bookprep-formatting.jpg, https://d1fd687oe6a92y.cloudfront.net/img/bookprep/bookprep-formatting%402x.jpg 2x" src="https://d1fd687oe6a92y.cloudfront.net/img/bookprep/bookprep-formatting%402x.jpg" alt="">
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-lg-8 order-2 order-lg-1">
                            <h1>What Is Formatting<br/> and Why Does It Matter?</h1>
                            <p>Formatting applies the right technical characteristics to your manuscript so that every word and every setting is correct and consistent. Formatting also scrubs out the invisible underlying errors that accumulate as you save and resave your file with each new draft. A final, formatted file looks clean and polished on-screen—but more importantly, it behaves and looks clean and polished when printed or when converted for e-reading.</p>
                            <p class="format-file">No matter your platform, you’ll need a fully formatted file prepared to exact technical specifications before you can publish. Avoid aggravation and delays—let Kirkus format and prep your files for you!</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
