            <section class="faq">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-12">
                            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                            <h3>Why do I need formatting?</h3>
                            <p>Every publishing platform requires a fully formatted file prepared to their exact technical specifications before you can publish. Why? An unformatted file may look right on your screen, but it can shed important characteristics like italics, spacing, and font styles when it’s processed for printing or e-reading. Formatting ensures your published book is beautiful, polished, and correct.</p>
                            <h3>When should I submit my book for formatting?</h3>
                            <p>Formatting is your very last step before publication. The manuscript you submit for formatting should be the exact manuscript you wish to publish—a completely clean final draft. Any changes to your file after formatting can introduce technical errors, so wait to submit your book for formatting until you’re ready to publish.</p>
                            <h3>How long does formatting take?</h3>
                            <p>Each book is different, and more complex books generally take more time to design. Standard formatting projects typically take two weeks from start to finish. Custom design projects typically take three to four weeks.</p>
                            <h3>Does Kirkus edit or proofread my manuscript during formatting?</h3>
                            <p>Our technical editors and designers will be solely focused on the visual and technical aspects of your document. They will not edit or proofread your manuscript, and any editorial corrections you request after formatting will incur additional costs. We highly recommend a professional edit before you submit your book for formatting.</p>
                            <h3>What types of files do I need to submit?</h3>
                            <p>Manuscripts should be submitted in Microsoft Word format. Tables and other text-based design elements (such as captions, sidebars, or pull quotes) should be included in the manuscript. Images, illustrations, and graphics—including charts and graphs—can be embedded in the manuscript to demonstrate their placement, but every image, illustration, or graphic must also be submitted as a print-ready TIF, PNG, or JPG.</p>
                            <h3>What makes an image print-ready?</h3>
                            <p class="pb-0"><strong>Images are print-ready when they meet the following requirements:</strong></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>High resolution—at least 300 dpi</li>
                                <li>Full size—as large or larger than the size at which they will be printed</li>
                                <li>True color—full color, grayscale, or black-and-white to match how they will be printed</li>
                                <li>Flat—no layers or transparencies are present</li>
                                <li>TIF, PNG, or JPG format</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Keep in mind that our formatting and design services do not include any photo preparation or manipulation services, and they do not include any image licensing or permissions. Refer to our handy guidelines as you prepare your images for publication.</p>
                            <h3>My manuscript has a lot of complex elements, like notes, tables, and equations. Can your services accommodate that?</h3>
                            <p>Absolutely. No matter what the interior of your book includes, our services provide a professional design and a complete technical makeover to make publishing easy and improve your readers’ experience.</p>
                            <h3>If Kirkus formats my book, does that make Kirkus my publisher?</h3>
                            <p>Kirkus is not a publisher, and the final files you receive from us at the end of your service are not published until you publish them through the platform of your choice. You do not assign us any ownership or rights to your content when you engage our services. No matter which platform you select, our formatting and design services can prepare your files to make publishing practically carefree.</p>

                            <h4>Need Help?</h4>
                            <p>Contact us: <a href="tel:1-888-407-4474">888-407-4474</a> or email <a href="mailto:bookediting@kirkus.com">bookediting@kirkus.com</a>.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
